st:1: additional directions
tb: On Ember Days or other occasions, if desired, the Litany of Ordinations
    may be used in place of the Prayers of the People at the Eucharist, or
    following the Collects in the Daily Office, or it may be used separately.
tb: A maniple may also be bestowed at the vesting of a Priest or a Bishop.
tb: When the Priest or Deacon being ordained is to be immediately
    instituted as Rector, the rite of the Institution of a Rector is not used.
    Instead, the Bishop reads the Letter of Institution (page 514) before the
    Peace during the Ordination liturgy.
